summary: Hey @taylorswift, I’m well aware that you have no clue who I am, so let me introduce myself. My name is Jessica, Jess for short...
caption:
Hey @taylorswift,

I’m well aware that you have no clue who I am, so let me introduce myself. My name is Jessica, Jess for short and because I like you, feel free to also call me Jessie. I am a 23 year old Australian fan who is attending your Sydney show on November 2nd. I’m currently a university student completing a double degree in law and psychology but I also love reading and creative writing which is in part why I love your music and poems so much.

While I want to keep this short, I was hoping to tell you a bit more about myself in case I never get the chance to in person. Let’s start with the bad shall we? I’m someone who has come from a less well off and toxic family to the point I no longer speak to my father, sister and extended family. I’ve also faced a range of differing abuses including sexual, physical and emotional from ex friends, family members and others. And finally, when I was fifteen, I lost two friends to death; one through a brain tumor and one through suicide which I unfortunately witnessed. As you can imagine, these kind of traumas leave an impact and have left me with Post Traumatic Stress Disorder and Bipolar Disorder.

Now I want to make it clear that I am not saying this for some form of pity points or to guilt trip you. I’m saying this because I honestly feel like I’m the luckiest person in the world. And I know that sounds strange coming off what I just said, but it’s true. Because while I have had all of these awful things happen to me, I have also experienced some of the most beautiful moments in life, some of which happened this year and are in the photos in this post. Due to a change in financial situations in the last few years, I’ve been able to travel to 4 countries outside Australia (New Caledonia, England, America and Japan) and 2 states outside my own but within Australia multiple times (Victoria and New South Wales). Additionally, I have been lucky enough to see several incredible artists perform this year (let alone other years) including Ed, Bruno, P!nk and most recently Kesha. Hell, the fact that I have the option to even go to university is such a privilege in my eyes. But most importantly, while I have had several shitty people in my life over the years, I have been so incredibly lucky to have the best loved ones you could ask for, including my paramedicine student friend coming with me to your show.

Finally, I have been lucky enough to have your music in my darkest moments. Over the years, every song of yours from I Knew You Were Trouble to Innocent and everything in between has helped me forgive myself for the things that weren’t my fault, accept the things I cannot change and recover from the traumas laid upon me. Earlier this year, I fell into a depressive episode that mirrored the mental state I had when I was 17, which was my worst. Being able to see you grow, recover and perform over the last few months has inspired me more than you can imagine and helped as I have also slowly recovered back to the point where I am mostly okay with my life and optimistic about the future.

Anyway, I feel like I’ve spoken too much so I just want to end this off by saying that I cannot wait to see you in Sydney and while the show is well and truly enough for me, if you want to catch up more, myself and my paramedicine friend will be in section 126-2, Row. 44, Seat/s.48-49.

Hi Taylor! @taylorswift @taylornation I am Hayley.A Swiftie from Hong...
body:
About Grateful and FEARLESS —My Little Taylor Swift Story

Hi Taylor! @taylorswift @taylornation I am Hayley.A Swiftie from Hong Kong 🇭🇰

I’ve been a huge fan since i was in secondary school☺️. Now I am studying in third year of my bachelor’s degree ☺️. Through this three years, I have come across many suddenly occurrences. Including my HKDSE exam and my part time job.

✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨

Thank you Taylor. Your songs gives me a huge of contentment. And let me know that the world aren’t all sunshine and rainbows. All sufferings have their reward. I am so grateful to be a swiftie. You are my role model>3

💫💫💫💫💫💫💫💫💫💫💫💫💫💫

And I hope one day I can say thank you to you!

Taylor☺️,I will be flying from Hong Kong🇭🇰 to Sydney. Traveling 9 hours and 7381KM to see you☺️!!!

My seat is Section A7,Row R,Seat24☺️☺️☺️So close to the stage and I am so excited!!!

SYDNEY IS READY FOR IT,and so am I!!!

Can’t wait to listen what the surprise song is😍😍✨✨✨(My favourite is Sparks Fly!✨💫💖)

See you on NOV 2nd !!!
